radio_data.name: Head Radio
radio_data.Observations: is_music is used to tell when not to play music on twitch audio track 2 (?), only 1, where it is not saved in vods, is_ambient_sound is used to tell when to play ambient sounds on both tracks 1 and 2, only if is_music is false, otherwise, it'll play only on track 2, loop is used to tell when a track should loop, in most cases, it should only loop when there's music, but there are a few music tracks that do not actually loop ingame, it should not loop in cutscene dialogs, mission completion jingles, news broadcasts, etc, start_over is used to tell if an audio should play from the beginning when it's played or if it should continue from where it left off, first_play_start_position is used to tell where in the file the music should start playing when it is played for the first time, radio uses music volume but cutscenes use sfx volume... thanks rockstar..., however I found SFX and Radio addresses that can be edited and will take effect in real time, sfx_volume and radio_volume are used to tell what volumes should be set to what whenever there's a audio track change
